                            <comment id="17147882" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 29 Jun 2020 15:26:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix is pretty simple, we can just skip the validation if the table has a KEYS index. More importantly, I&apos;ve added a dtest to test the upgrade path of KEYS 2i to 4.0, which in particular demonstrates the problem described (as DROP COMPACT STORAGE is part of that upgrade path).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;C* patch&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;dtest patch&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;CI&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pcmanus/cassandra/commits/C-15906-3.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pcmanus/cassandra-dtest/commits/test_keys_2i_upgrade&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-cassandra.apache.org/job/Cassandra-devbranch/169/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;#169&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Note that there is only a 3.0 patch since as said in the description, 3.11+ is not affected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
